EDIT: this is now resolved.

The current implementation seems to be using the aggregate pubkey (before the tweaks) inside the key of the `PSBT_IN_MUSIG2_PUB_NONCE` (and I'd assume `PSBT_IN_MUSIG2_PARTIAL_SIGNATURE`, but I didn't reach there, yet); instead, [BIP-373](https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0373.mediawiki) says that it must be _the key found in the script and not the aggregate public key that it was derived from, if it was derived from an aggregate key_. Therefore, I interpreted it as the taproot pubkey for a keypath spend, and the exact key that appears in the tapleaf for a scriptspend.

Using the aggregate key pre-tweaks could be problematic if the same aggregate key appears multiple times, for example in something like:
```tr(NUMS/<0;1>/*,or_d(pk(musig(A,B)/<0;1>/*),pk(musig(A,B)/<2;3>/*)))```
Here, the two musigs have the same participants, and same aggregate key pre-tweaks (and they are in the same leaf, so even the tapleaf_hash won't help); only the tweaks allow the disambiguation.

